 MBOMBELA – Hawks spokesman, Capt Dineo Sekgotodi said Freeman Thulani Maisane  who was arrested by Members of Mpumalanga Hawks and TRT Nelspruit for the murder of  the late Sgt Thembisile Ndlovu (40) and her husband Jabulani Khoza (44) and for the possession of unlicensed firearm. The couple were awoken by a disruption inside their house. “Upon inspection they were fired upon by three suspects. The late Detective Ndlovu was from Calcutta SAPS retaliated and fatally wounded one suspect.” ALSO READ: Five-year-old girl mauled to death by pitbulls in White River The other two armed suspects continued firing, and both Ndlovu and Khoza succumbed to injuries from the shooting. “The suspects fled the scene with the family’s vehicle, which was later found abandoned within the Bushbuckridge area.” The Hawks, assisted by the Nelspruit Tactical Response Team (TRT), arrested Maisane for the alleged murder and possession of an unlicensed firearm.
“He was found at his hiding place in Mhluzi (Middelburg) in the early hours of Saturday.” ALSO READ: UPDATE: Stray hippo that was captured, dies The national head of the Hawks, Lt Gen Godfrey Lebeya, has commended the investigating team for the apprehension of the alleged perpetrator and is confident that the third suspect will be arrested soon. The case was transferred to Thulamahashe (Mhala Magistrate Court) for a formal bail application on both cases of murder and possession of unlicensed firearm.